jobs.title: Art
duties: Leonardo da Vinci believed that seeing was important, and his idea was inevitable that it would result in opening and looking into everything known.
He studied the animal bodies, then sneaked the bodies of people who had just died from the graves and used them as cadavers.

What he did in the medieval world was extremely dangerous because 100 years after that, Galileo's scientific ideas about the structure of the solar system and general relativity caused him to live in conviction.
